  "text": "[Vue compat] @click not working on a component\n\n### Version\r\n3.2.11\r\n\r\n### Reproduction link\r\n[codesandbox.io](https://codesandbox.io/s/wizardly-kilby-mbsy6?file=/src/App.vue:227-243)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\nClicking on \"click mee\"\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\n Should log \"click\" in the console\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\nNot doing anything\r\n\r\n---\r\nI tried adding `COMPILER_V_ON_NATIVE: false` to vue.config.js but it seems to make no difference. This issue only happens in the compat build of vue\r\n\r\n<!-- generated by vue-issues. DO NOT REMOVE -->",
